 #Deployment Instructions: Google Cloud Platform
  # Deployment on Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
 1. Set up a new project on GCP and enable Cloud Run and Firestore.
 2. Install the Google Cloud SDK: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install
 3. Authenticate with your GCP account: `gcloud auth login`
 4. Deploy the backend to Cloud Run:
   ```
   gcloud run deploy greencart-backend --source . --platform managed --region
 us-central1
   ```
5. Set up MongoDB on Atlas and connect it to the backend.
 6. Configure environment variables for Stripe keys and MongoDB URI in Cloud Run.
 7. Test the deployment and ensure the frontend and backend communicate smoothly
